Cyn and all

I am always a little reluctant to tell my stories because I almost
always get the feeling that people don't believe me and when you are
describing what actually happened that can be a little off putting
however--

One of the funniest happened one morning when I got up much the worst
for wear from the night before. The house was built between 1795 and
1798 and the back part of the house had settle much more than the
front part. I had a little den that had once been part of a back
porch. the pitch of the floor was so much in that room that I had a
brick under the legs on one end of the couch and even then you did
tend to list a little.On the up side of that room there was a door
that opened into long center hallway. this door opened uphill and
always stuck. it took a little effort to open it. this particular
morning as i walked into the den that door opened by itself. I held
my poor head and said aloud &quot;I am not in the mood for this!&quot;
Whereupon the door closed. The knob turned and the door closed very
guietly. i said &quot;thanks&quot; and made coffee.

Maryann

