"/> We had a spook in our Victorian house that only my little brother had
seen standing outside the house. One early morning @ 2am I was getting a
ride home with a friend, as we pulled up toward the front of my house
someone wearing a fedora ( Indiana Jones style) and a trench coat al la
Bogart walked from the front door around the front of my van. Before the
eyes of my friend and myself the figure faded from it's feet to the
middle and from the tip of it's hat to the middle and vanished. From
were we sat it looked almost like someone quickly ducking out of sight ,
so we both jumped out of the cab of his truck , my friend ran around the
left side of my house and I ran around the right , hoping to catch the
'Intruder' in the back yard. Neither one of us saw the intruder on our
pursuit and met one another in the back yard. Now comes the freaky part,
it had been raining off and on all day, the only footprints in the mud
were ours, no other prints were found anywhere on the property. After
our encounter we put on the kettle and went over what we both saw and
came to the conclusion that , #1 we were both sober &amp; straight and had
seen something beyond explanation and #2 we now had a good excuse to
get drunk or high. We still talk about it every now and again when
Autumn is in the air, we always have a drink afterwards.
