"/> Absolutely, but here goes (again for some r.a. members):

I was riding my motorbike home late at night on the Isle of Wight, and
got to the top of a long hill covered over by trees. Just as I got to
the bottom a woman stepped right out in front of me. I braked so hard
that I lost control of the bike and it skidded over on its side. After
asecond I thought &quot;Oh no, I must have killed her. I couldn't see
anything as it was so dark, so I pointed the headlight around....and
there was nothing there. I was frightened because I thought I had
really hit someone and more frightened thinking that she had been
thrown into a ditch. I roared off home thinking either I had made it
all up or that this would be in the paper the next day..it wasn't.

A couple of years later, I had been playing guitar off the Island, and
someone on the car ferry offered to give me a lift home. Again it was
night and we soon reached the same spot where I had my 'experience'.
The driver turned to his friend and said jokingly &quot;Isn't this supposed
tobe where you see the &quot;White Lady&quot;?! Now I was really scared.

Apparently, last century, a woman had thrown herself in front of a
horse and cart at that exact spot.

I can't explain this...I know what I saw...and I had no knowledge of
any stories connected with this road......

Jon

