There is one story I can never tell because I don't want to worry my
children...and yet I realise that this is my chance to 'get it off my
chest'.

The old house we live in was owned by two elderly sisters. Mary
outlived her sister Clara who had died before I bought the house. Mary
lived with us until she was 100, and I had to restore the house around
her. She loved this, especially talking to various plumbers and
electricians I had in from time to time.

However, whenever I was working upstairs on my own, I would hear
footsteps, the door would open (latch and all) and I KNEW that Clara
was standing there watching me. I could not see her. At first this
really spooked me, but then I kept talking to her as I got this really
lonely feeling...I even showed her the improvements I was making. I
kept telling her how happy Mary was and that she would soon be with
her again. Finally, one day, she did frighten me by running up the
stairs and bursting into the room. I yelled out loud &quot;Clara, I'm fed
up with you checking onme all the time, and it frightens me...you know
that we are looking after Mary and the house. NOW GO AWAY!!....and she
did, that minute.
From then on the house has had a warm and contented feeling which many
people comment on.

Jon

PS It still makes the hair on my neck go up thinking of all those
times when the door would open and I knew that someone was behind me
whilstI painted or plastered and all the silly conversations that I
had....&quot;Look, Clara it's pink...is that all right with you?&quot;..then the
door closing again after she had satisfied herself that the work was
progressing well.

