"/> Mike--I found that whenever something happened I would try very hard
to come up with rational reasons why what happened was a natural
event. Maybe when I opened the door to the den I created a draft or
maybe we had a tiny earthquake; maybe when I saw &quot;Nanna&quot; watching me
in the garden from the dinning room window it really was just a
reflection--anything to keep from having to deal with the possibility
of the supernatural. But the one event that I can never find a
rationl reason for was the day I went into the library and found three
books in the middle of the floor. I lived alone and had had no
company for a while. the books were stacked neatly in the very middle
of the room. No way could they have fallen from any of the shelves
and landed where they were. And even if they had fallen, no way could
they land neatly stacked with the biggest on the bottom and the
smallest on the top. that on still makes my hands shake a little!

Maryann

