The first time I realized that my life was going to be weird was when I
inherited my maternal Grandmother's high school yearbook. She committed
suicide when my father was an infant. It's a lovely red-leather bound
book. I kept it on a bookshelf.

One day I came home from work (I lived alone at the time) and the book
had *magically* moved itself from the bookcase to my coffee table. Not
only that, it was opened to the single page which had been signed by my
