anything there. Eventually the weight would lift, there'd be a soft
'thud' by my bed and the creaking would return the way it came. My
father didn't believe in anything that couldn't be bought sold or
traded, but even he admitted to seeing 'phantom' (the name I'd given it)
on several occasions. My mother heard him scratching at my door one
night until he nudged it open. His silhouette in the doorway was
something we'd both seen, her from one side of the doorway, and me, from
the other. For about 2 years 'Phantom' was a regular 'guest' in the
house. (never needed a litter box either!) Then one day, he just stopped
coming.
